ed-4489583%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Flife-of-gaza-uprising-icon-jamal-al-durrah-lost-son-mohammad-al-durrah-23-years-ago-now-5-of-family-killed-4489583%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Flife-of-gaza-uprising-icon-jamal-al-durrah-lost-son-mohammad-al-durrah-23-years-ago-now-5-of-family-killed-4489583%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20Opinion%3A%20Right%20To%20Life%20Of%20Unborn%20Vs%20Woman's%20Autonomy%20-%20No%20Easy%20Answers%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20rejected%20a%20woman's%20request%20to%20terminate%20her%2026-week%20pregnancy%20under%20the%20Medical%20Termination%20of%20Pregnancy%20Act%2C1971%20(MTP%20Act)%2C%20noting%20that%20there%20was%20neither%20any%20danger%20to%20her%20life%20nor%20any%20foetal%20abnormality.%20Under%20the%20law%2C%20a%20pregnancy%20can%20be%20ended%20up%20to%2024%20weeks%20for%20married%20women%20and%20special%20categories%20like%20rape%20survivors%2C%20minors%20and%20the%20differently-abled.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20had%20sought%20a%20fresh%20medical%20report%20from%20Delhi's%20AIIMS%20hospital%20to%20understand%20the%20foetal%20health%20and%20medical%20conditions%20of%20the%2027-year-old%20married%20woman%2C%20a%20mother%20of%20two%2C%20who%20stood%20firm%20on%20her%20plea%20for%20immediate%20termination%20of%20her%20pregnancy.%20On%20October%2011%2C%20a%20division%20bench%20delivered%20a%20split%20verdict.%20The%20AIIMS%20medical%20board%20confirmed%20that%20the%20petitioner%20was%20suffering%20from%20post-partum%20psychosis.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20faced%20the%20dilemma%20of%20whether%20to%20allow%20the%20woman%20to%20terminate%20the%20foetus%20and%20in%20the%20process%2C%20pondered%20over%20the%20woman's%20right%20to%20life%2C%20which%20involves%20her%20body%20on%20one%20hand%20and%20the%20rights%20of%20an%20unborn%20child%20on%20the%20other.%20The%20judges%20said%20that%20they%20couldn't%20infringe%20on%20the%20rights%20of%20the%20baby%20(foetus)%20to%20protect%20the%20rights%20of%20the%20pregnant%20woman%20-%20mentioning%20the%20need%20to%20find%20a%20'balance'%20between%20the%20two.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20the%20woman's%20body%20and%20she%20should%20have%20the%20control%20of%20making%20decisions%20for%20it.%20If%20she%20has%20willingly%20or%20accidentally%20conceived%2C%20her%20consent%20to%20give%20birth%20is%20imperative.%20What%20is%20the%20point%20of%20having%20a%20child%20if%20the%20biological%20mother%20can't%20give%20affection%20and%20properly%20bring%20up%20the%20kid%3F%20It%20will%20defeat%20the%20purpose%20of%20forcing%20a%20woman%20to%20continue%20her%20pregnancy%20if%20it%20can%20be%20medically%20terminated%20without%20endangering%20her%20life.%20There%20are%20unsaid%20mental%20consequences%20on%20the%20lives%20of%20the%20mother%20and%20the%20child%20which%20should%20not%20be%20lost%20sight%20of%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Rohini%20Wagh%2C%20Supreme%20Court%20lawyer.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20considered%20all%20aspects%20of%20the%20case%20but%20seems%20to%20have%20given%20importance%20to%20the%20viability%20of%20the%20foetus%20over%20the%20mental%20health%20issues%20that%20the%20woman%20might%20face%20after%20the%20baby's%20birth.%20In%20fact%2C%20the%20mental%20well-being%20of%20the%20mother%20will%20directly%20impact%20the%20psychological%20well-being%20of%20the%20child%20through%20life%20and%20it%20is%20a%20point%20that%20needs%20serious%20consideration.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20a%20doctor%20had%20confirmed%20that%20there%20could%20be%20consequences%2C%20we%20needed%20to%20introspect%20on%20the%20woman's%20mental%20health%2C%20otherwise%20there's%20no%20point%20having%20a%20Mental%20Health%20Act.%20When%20there%20is%20an%20absolute%20urgency%20to%20do%20this%20kind%20of%20termination%2C%20the%20woman%20alone%20should%20be%20at%20the%20centre%20and%20whatever%20option%20-%20conducive%2C%20probable%2C%20feasible%20and%20not-so-risky%20-%20should%20be%20given%20to%20her.%20Society%2C%20judiciary%2C%20police%2C%20and%20family%20should%20just%20stand%20in%20solidarity%20behind%20her%20and%20support%20her.%20It%20should%20not%20be%20a%20choice%20just%20for%20the%20sake%20of%20choice%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Nikhil%20Datar%2C%20a%20Mumbai-based%20gynaecologist%20who%20has%20been%20at%20the%20forefront%20of%20the%20campaign%20and%20involved%20in%20324%20court%20cases%20in%20this%20issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20said%20parents%20can%20make%20the%20decision%20of%20whether%20to%20give%20the%20child%20up%20for%20adoption%20or%20raise%20it.%20A%20closer%20look%20would%20lead%20us%20to%20believe%20that%20this%20Catch-22%20choice%20is%20tough%20on%20parents.%20Carrying%20the%20baby%20full-term%2C%20having%20it%20and%20then%20giving%20it%20up%20for%20adoption%20is%20not%20a%20choice%20any%20parent%20would%20want%20to%20make%20-%20both%20scenarios%20could%20mentally%20scar%20them%20for%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEach%20case%20has%20to%20be%20judged%20on%20its%20own%20facts%20and%20even%20trained%20judicial%20minds%20can%20arrive%20at%20diametrically%20opposite%20views%2C%20as%20the%20present%20case%20has%20shown.%20At%20the%20core%20of%20the%20debate%20is%20the%20autonomy%20of%20the%20woman%20over%20her%20own%20body%20and%20the%20rights%20of%20the%20unborn%20child%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Aparajita%20Singh%2C%20Senior%20Advocate%2C%20Supreme%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHowever%2C%20one%20wonders%20what%20meaning%20the%20right%20of%20the%20unborn%20child%20has%20when%20the%20mother%20delivers%20it%20only%20to%20give%20it%20up%20for%20adoption%20in%20a%20country%20where%20the%20process%20of%20adoption%20takes%20years%20to%20complete%2C%20as%20observed%20recently%20by%20the%20Chief%20Justice.%20In%20the%20case%2C%20the%20petitioner%20argued%20that%20according%20to%20the%20report%20of%20the%20Parliamentary%20Standing%20Committee%20in%20Rajya%20Sabha%2C%203.1%20crore%20children%20are%20waiting%20to%20be%20adopted%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Ms%20Singh.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20judiciary%20has%20addressed%20the%20question%20of%20law%20in%20this%20case.%20Now%20it%20is%20up%20to%20the%20legislature%20to%20consider%20amending%20the%20law%20so%20that%20the%2024-week%20limit%20is%20widened%20to%20factor%20in%20other%20sensitivities.%20Many%20factors%20were%20not%20considered%20when%20the%20courts%20decided%20the%20merits%20of%20the%20cases.%20It%20might%20take%20years%20before%20the%20paradigm%20shifts%20in%20these%20matters%20-%20till%20then%2C%20progressive%20judicial%20interpretations%20will%20govern%20each%20case%2C%20maybe%20differently.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20married%20woman%20asking%20for%20termination%20of%20pregnancy%20is%20in%20need.%20The%20circumstances%20-%20mental%2C%20physical%2C%20social%20-%20around%20her%20are%20such%20that%20she%20is%20in%20need%20of%20this%20particular%20procedure%20otherwise%20no%20woman%20would%20like%20to%20undergo%20a%20medical%20procedure%20unnecessarily.%20Only%20because%20someone's%20application%20to%20terminate%20is%20delayed%2C%20it%20should%20not%20be%20declined%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Dr%20Datar.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20it%20is%20viable%20in%2024%20weeks%2C%20it%20can%20also%20be%20done%20after%20that.%20The%20court%20should%20decide%20the%20conditions%20for%20terminating%20the%20pregnancy%20beforehand.%20If%20the%20woman%20in%20need%20fits%20those%20conditions%20she%20should%20be%20allowed%20to%20terminate%20the%20pregnancy%20and%20nothing%20else%20should%20come%20in%20her%20way.%20If%20the%20rights%20of%20an%20unborn%20foetus%20have%20to%20be%20considered%2C%20then%20even%20a%20seven-week-old%20foetus%20has%20that%20right.%20Why%20wait%2024%20weeks%3F%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20ruling%20allowing%20the%20foetus%20to%20complete%20its%20full%20natural%20gestation%20cycle%2C%20categorically%20denying%20the%20right%20of%20the%20woman%20to%20decide%20on%20her%20body%2C%20has%20firmly%20established%20another%20legal%20precedent.%20But%20one%20cannot%20miss%20the%20unanswered%20questions%2C%20especially%20those%20that%20involve%20the%20mental%20well-being%20of%20the%20would-be%20mother%2C%20as%20validated%20by%20the%20psychiatrist%20at%20AIIMS.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMost%20of%20the%20stakeholders%20in%20this%20saga%20won't%20track%20the%20developments%20beyond%20the%20court%2C%20but%20it%20may%20not%20be%20an%20easy%20ride%20for%20a%20baby%20whose%20mother%20has%20fought%20to%20prevent%20it%20from%20coming%20into%20this%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Bharti%20Mishra%20Nath%20is%20a%20senior%20journalist)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697550600000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.ndtvimg.com%2Fi%2F2016-05%2Fabortion-afp_650x400_41463552360.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fright-to-life-of-unborn-vs-womans-autonomy-no-easy-answers-4489892%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20rejected%20a%20woman's%20request%20to%20terminate%20her%2026-week%20pregnancy%20under%20the%20Medical%20Termination%20of%20Pregnancy%20Act%2C1971%20(MTP%20Act)%2C%20noting%20that%20there%20was%20neither%20any%20danger%20to%20her%20life%20nor%20any%20foetal%20abnormality.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fright-to-life-of-unborn-vs-womans-autonomy-no-easy-answers-4489892%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Scientists%20to%20use%20solar%20fusion%20to%20make%20moon%20roads%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697550471000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-104502679%2Cimgsize-67572.cms%22%2C%22o