%20according%20to%20surveys%2C%20company%20data%2C%20and%20drivers'%20accounts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EMillennials%20are%20the%20most%20likely%20generation%20to%20be%20gig%20drivers%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223252%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20Uber%20driver%20and%20car%20with%20passengers.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64e8ebd7bc26b40019901b64%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222251%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20Uber%20driver%20with%20passengers.%3Cp%3ERobert%20Alexander%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EA%202021%20Pew%20Research%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Finternet%2F2021%2F12%2F08%2Fthe-state-of-gig-work-in-2021%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esurvey%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20over%2010%2C000%20adults%20found%20that%2018%25%20of%2018-%20to%2029-year-olds%20had%20worked%20for%20a%20delivery%20platform%2C%20compared%20to%207%25%20of%2030-%20to%2049-year-olds.%20Nine%20percent%20of%2018-%20to%2029-year-olds%20and%206%25%20of%2030-%20to%2049-year-olds%C2%A0surveyed%20by%20Pew%20had%20driven%20for%20a%20ride-hailing%20app.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGiven%20that%20many%20more%20millennials%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fshort-reads%2F2019%2F01%2F17%2Fwhere-millennials-end-and-generation-z-begins%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eborn%20between%201981%20and%201996%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20are%20of%20working%20age%20than%20Gen%20Zers%20%E2%80%94%20born%20between%201997%20and%202012%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20likely%20that%20there%20are%20more%20millennial%20gig%20drivers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMen%20and%20women%20were%20equally%20as%20likely%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eto%20have%20worked%20as%20delivery%20drivers%2C%20while%20men%20were%20slightly%20more%20likely%20to%20have%20driven%20for%20a%20ride-hailing%20app%2C%20according%20to%20Pew.%20Additionally%2C%20Hispanic%20people%20were%20the%20most%20likely%20to%20have%20worked%20as%20gig%20drivers%3A%2016%25%20of%20Hispanic%20people%20surveyed%20said%20they%20had%20worked%20as%20a%20delivery%20driver%2C%20compared%20to%2010%25%20of%20Black%2C%207%25%20of%20Asian%2C%20and%204%25%20of%20white%20respondents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20typical%20gig%20driver%20earns%20between%20%2420%20and%20%2440%20an%20hour%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Sergio%20Avedian%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64418aa4632fda001803d84f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221469%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESergio%20Avedian.%3Cp%3ESergio%20Avedian%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20in%20lower-income%20tiers%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20work%20as%20gig%20drivers%20than%20people%20in%20higher%20income%20brackets%2C%20according%20to%20Pew.%20Eight%20percent%20of%20those%20surveyed%20who%20were%20considered%20low-income%20earners%20had%20driven%20for%20a%20ride-hailing%20platform%2C%20compared%20to%204%25%20of%20middle-income%20and%202%25%20of%20upper-income%20earners.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20survey%20classified%2032%25%20of%20respondents%20as%20low%20income%20and%2046%25%20as%20middle%20income%2C%20so%20the%20ratio%20of%20low-income%20drivers%20is%20likely%20higher.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20typical%20Uber%20driver%20earns%20%2435%20per%20active%20%E2%80%94%20or%20utilized%20%E2%80%94%20hour%2C%20the%20company%20said%20in%20February.%20In%20September%2C%20a%20Lyft%20representative%20told%20Insider%20that%20including%20tips%20and%20bonuses%2C%20the%20average%20US%20driver%20makes%20close%20to%20%2436%20an%20active%20hour.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20ride-hailing%20drivers%20previously%20told%20Insider%20that%20they%20use%20their%20online%20work%20hours%20%E2%80%94%20the%20time%20they%20have%20the%20app%20open%20%E2%80%94%20to%20determine%20their%20per-hour%20pay.%20They%20said%20this%20provides%20a%20more%20accurate%20reflection%20of%20their%20per-hour%20earnings.%20Additionally%2C%20the%20figures%20Uber%20and%20Lyft%20provided%20don't%20account%20for%20vehicle%20expenses%20like%20gas%20and%20maintenance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESergio%20Avedian%2C%20an%20Uber%20driver%20who%20is%20a%20senior%20contributor%20to%20the%20gig-driver-advocacy%20blog%20and%20YouTube%20channel%20The%20Rideshare%20Guy%2C%20told%20Insider%20that%20based%20on%20his%20research%20in%20Los%20Angeles%2C%20the%20typical%20driver%20earns%20between%20%2422%20and%20%2425%20an%20hour%20before%20expenses.%20He%20said%20vehicle%20expenses%20like%20gas%20and%20maintenance%20generally%20cost%20a%20driver%20%245%20to%20%247%20an%20hour.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20drivers%20have%20had%20better%20luck%2C%20however.%20In%20September%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuber-lyft-drivers-explain-how-they-make-the-most-money-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Efour%20ride-hailing%20drivers%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20told%20Insider%20that%20they%20earn%20between%20%2422%20to%20%2440%20an%20hour%20after%20expenses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20DoorDash%20spokesperson%20said%20in%20April%20that%20delivery%20drivers%20earn%20an%20average%20of%20%2425%20an%20hour%20before%20expenses.%20Drivers%20who%20work%20part%20time%20%E2%80%94%20or%20are%20more%20picky%20with%20which%20orders%20they%20accept%20%E2%80%94%20can%20sometimes%20see%20higher%20hourly%20earnings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20typical%20gig%20driver%20doesn't%20have%20other%20income%20and%20is%20trying%20out%20multiple%20apps%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222667%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20DoorDash%20delivery%20driver%20in%20New%20York%20City%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F652817e36561dd877e790f1c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20DoorDash%20delivery%20driver%20in%20New%20York%20City%3Cp%3ERibeiro%2FNew%20York%20Daily