20as%20a%20skeletal%20man%20clearly%20grasping%20his%20penis.%20%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F652e66a78bed706e837e0c81%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22853%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20photograph%20taken%20on%20October%209%2C%202023%20at%20the%20archaeological%20site%20of%20Karahantepe%20in%20Sanliurfa%2C%20southeastern%20Turkey%2C%20shows%20newly%20found%202.3-meter%20high%20human%20statue%3Cp%3EOZAN%20KOSE%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFinding%20statues%20like%20this%20is%20not%20uncommon%2C%20%26quot%3Bbut%20for%20the%20first%20time%20here%20we%20found%20the%20phallus%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20archaeologist%20Necmi%20Karul%20of%20Istanbul%20University%20who%20uncovered%20the%20statue%2C%20according%20to%20Agence%20France%20Presse%20(AFP).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ENeolithic%20humans%20may%20have%20been%20more%20sophisticated%20than%20we%20thought%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20just%20the%20latest%20discovery%20from%20a%20controversial%20site%20that%20could%20rewrite%20what%20we%20know%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fskull-cult-ancient-temple-neolithic-site-turkey-2017-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENeolithic%20culture%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKarahan%20Tepe%2C%20found%20in%20the%20Germu%C5%9F%20mountains%20of%20south-eastern%20Turkey%20near%20the%20border%20with%20Syria%2C%20is%20part%20of%20a%20sprawling%20archaeological%20project%20called%20Tas%20Tepe%2C%20comprising%20a%20dozen%20sites%20including%20Gobekli%20Tepe%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwhc.unesco.org%2Fen%2Flist%2F1572%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20UNESCO%20World%20Heritage%20site%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20area%20is%20known%20for%20its%20plethora%20of%20depictions%20of%20the%20male%20reproductive%20organ.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fturkey-is-building-a-wall-along-its-border-to-keep-out-isis-militants-2015-7%3Fr%3DUS%26IR%3DT%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUrfa%20man%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%206.2-foot-tall%20statue%20of%20a%20man%20seeming%20to%20protect%20his%20erect%20penis%20with%20both%20hands%2C%20was%20notably%20found%20nearby.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221285%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22a%20statue%20presented%20on%20a%20plinth%2C%20seemingly%20in%20a%20museum%2C%20represents%20a%20square%20shouldered%20man%20with%20a%20collar%20around%20his%20neck%20looking%20forward%20as%20both%20his%20hands%20are%20placed%20outstretched%20near%20his%20penis.%20%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F652e65c88bed706e837e0c5f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22856%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUrfa%20man%2C%20also%20known%20as%20the%20Balikligol%20statue%2C%20is%20shown%20in%20at%20Archeology%20Museum%20in%20Sanliurfa%20on%20February%2022%2C%202023.%3Cp%3EEsber%20Ayaydin%2FAnadolu%20Agency%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EKarahan%20Tepe%20itself%20is%20strewn%20with%20bizarre%20scenes%2C%20including%20a%20room%20peppered%20with%20T-shaped%20pillars%2C%20oddly%20reminiscent%20of%20phalluses%2C%20facing%20a%20round%20head%20sticking%20out%20of%20the%20rock%20face%2C%20per%20journalist%20Sean%20Thomas%2C%20who%20wrote%20about%20his%20visit%20to%20the%20site%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.spectator.co.uk%2Farticle%2Fdoes-an-unknown-extraordinarily-ancient-civilisation-lie-buried-under-eastern-turkey-%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Spectator%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20site%20shows%20a%20face%20sticking%20out%20of%20a%20rock%20wall%20while%20T-shaped%20columns%20are%20placed%20in%20front%20of%20it.%20%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F652e68d08bed706e837e0d9c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20view%20of%20the%20archeological%20excavation%20site%20of%20Karahantepe%2C%20one%20of%20the%20important%20settlements%20of%20the%20Neolithic%20period%2C%20in%20Sanliurfa%2C%20Turkiye%20on%20September%2020%2C%202022%3Cp%3E%20Esber%20Ayaydin%2FAnadolu%20Agency%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EStatues%20of%20leopards%2C%20foxes%2C%20and%20snakes%20are%20also%20found%20adorning%20pillars%20of%20the%20site%2C%20per%20AFP.%20Some%20statues%20of%20leopards%20show%20the%20predators%20riding%20humans%20or%20putting%20their%20paws%20over%20their%20eyes%2C%20per%20Thomas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENo%20statues%20of%20women%20have%20been%20found%20at%20the%20site%2C%20though%20it's%20possible%20these%20were%20made%20out%20of%20wood%20and%20lost%20in%20time%2C%20Karul%20told%20AFP.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20is%20clear%20from%20the%20findings%20at%20these%20sites%20is%20that%20hunter-gatherer%20communities%20in%20southwest%20Asia%20at%20the%20time%20were%20a%20lot%20more%20sophisticated%20than%20archaeologists%20had%20once%20thought%2C%20said%20Benjamin%20Arbuckle%2C%20an%20anthropologist%20at%20the%20University%20of%20North%20Carolina%20at%20Chapel%20Hill%20who%20was%20not%20involved%20with%20the%20excavations%2C%20per%20Live%20Science.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20findings%20of%20Gobekli%20Tepe%20and%20Karahan%20Tepe%20over%20the%20past%2030%20years%20show%20that%20they%20were%20not%20the%20%26quot%3Brelatively%20simple%2C%20small%20in%20scale%2C%20and%20generally%20egalitarian%2C%26quot%3B%20culture%20they%20were%20thought%20to%20be%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20is%20not%20clear%20is%20what%20this%20site%20was%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20German%20archaeologist%20Klaus%20Schmidt%2C%20who%20took%20the%20lead%20on%20the%20research%20in%20the%20early%201990s%2C%20the%20site%20was%20%26quot%3Bthe%20first%20human-built%20holy%20place%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.smithsonianmag.com%2Fhistory%2Fgobekli-tepe-the-worlds-first-temple-83613665%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520place%2520is%2520called%2520Gobekli%2Cof%2520the%2520world%2527s%2520oldest%2520temple.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESmithsonian%20Magazine%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202008.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20uncovered%20many%20t-shaped%20pillars%2C%20statues%20of%20animals%2C%20some%20depictions%20of%20humans%2C%20as%20well%20as%20stone%20tools%20characteristic%20of%20hunter-gatherer%20societies.%20But%20what%20he%20didn't%20find%20was%20evidence%20that%20the%20site%20was%20regularly%20inhabited.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20led%20him%20to%20believe%20this%20was%20a%20site%20that%20people%20visited%20occasionally%2C%20not%20built%20for%20habitation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B'Gobekli%20Tepe%20upends%20our%20view%20of%20human%20history%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Schmidt%20to%20Thomas%20in%202006.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20always%20thought%20that%20agriculture%20came%20first%2C%20then%20civilization%3A%20farming%2C%20pottery%2C%20social%20hierarchies.%20But%20here%20it%20is%20reversed%2C%20it%20seems%20the%20ritual%20center%20came%20first%2C%20then%20when%20enough%20hunter-gathering%20people%20collected%20to%20worship%20%E2%80%93%20or%20so%20I%20believe%20%E2%80%93%20they%20realized%20they%20had%20to%20feed%20people.%20Which%20means%20farming.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20then%2C%20new%20findings%20have%20come%20to%20challenge%20this%20theory.%20Digs%20have%20started%20to%20uncover%20possible%20traces%20of%20human%20habitation%20near%20the%20site%2C%20Lee%20Clare%2C%20an%20archaeologist%20from%20the%20German%20Archaeological%20Institute%2C%20who%20worked%20on%20the%20dig%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Ftravel%2Farticle%2F20210815-an-immense-mystery-older-than-stonehenge%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20the%20BBC.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20site%2C%20then%2C%20could%20have%20been%20a%20place%20where%20hunter-gatherers%20were%20trying%20to%20grasp%20their%20way%20of%20life%20as%20others%20were%20moving%20slowly%20toward%20agriculture%2C%20Clare%20told%20the%20BBC.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20statue%20guards%20its%20mysterious%20meaning%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20clear%20what%20the%20statue%20was%20meant%20to%20represent%20and%20how%20it%20fits%20within%20this%20mysterious%20Neolithic%20culture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20found%20near%20a%20smaller%20statue%20of%20a%20vulture%2C%20which%20could%20mean%20it%20has%20some%20connection%20with%20death%2C%20per%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbasin.ktb.gov.tr%2FTR-350158%2Ftarihin-sifir-noktasinda-ilk-boyali-heykel-bulundu.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epress%20release%3C%2Fa%3E%20accompanying%20the%20finding%20and%20translated%20from%20Turkish.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Karul%2C%20it%20could%20be%20a%20way%20that%20humans%20at%20the%20time%20were%20starting%20to%20spiritually%20see%20themselves%20at%20the%20center%20of%20the%20animal%20world.%20For%20him%2C%20this%20could%20be%20a%20form%20of%20shamanistic%20ritual%2C%20though%20he%20wouldn't%20venture%20as%20far%20as%20calling%20it%20a%20religion%2C%20he%20told%20AFP.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETed%20Banning%2C%20an%20anthropologist%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Toronto%20who%20was%20not%20involved%20in%20the%20research%2C%20thinks%20the%20buildings%20at%20Karahan%20Tepe%20were%20more%20likely%20to%20be%20houses%20than%20temples.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20for%20him%2C%20the%20statue%20could%20be%20%26quot%3Ban%20important%20ancestor%20associated%20with%20the%20building%20in%20which%20it%20was%20found%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20per%20Live%20Science.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20fact%20that%20the%20figure%20is%20clutching%20its%20penis%20is%20also%20consistent%20with%20this%20interpretation%20by%20potentially%20symbolizing%20that%20this%20person%20was%20the%20progenitor%20of%20a%20social%20group%2C%20such%20as%20a%20lineage%20or%20clan%2C%20associated%20with%20the%20building%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20per%20Live%20Science.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBanning%20noted%2C%20however%2C%20that%20%26quot%3Bany%20interpretation%20of%20the%20statue%20is%20conjectural%20at%20this%20point%2C%26quot%3B%20per%20Live%20Science.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERegardless%20of%20its%20meaning%2C%20the%20discovery%20of%20the%20statue%2C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dainst.org%2Fen%2Fnewsroom%2Fnoslug%2F181%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20alongside%20another%20statue%20representing%20a%20boar%3C%2Fa%3E%20recently%20found%20in%20Gobekli%20Tepe%20%26quot%3Brepresent%20the%20latest%20spectacular%20finds%20from%20these%20sites%2C%20which%20are%20transforming%20our%20understanding%20of%20pre-agricultural%20communities%2C%26quot%3B%20Arbuckle%20said%2C%20per%20Live%20Science.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fancient-statue-of-man-holding-his-penis-could-reveal-neolithic-secrets-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697549282000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F652e67448bed706e837e0cd3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fancient-statue-of-man-holding-his-penis-could-reveal-neolithic-secrets-2023-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20statue%20was%20found%20in%20what%20some%20argue%20are%20the%20oldest%20Neolithic%20temple%20sites%20in%20the%20world%2C%20older%20than%20the%20Egyptian%20pyramids%20and%20Stonehenge.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22mguenot%40businessinsider.com%20(Marianne%20Guenot)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fancient-statue-of-man-holding-his-penis-could-reveal-neolithic-secrets-2023-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20had%202%20limbs%20amputated%20after%20an%20accident.%20A%20year%20later%20I've%20returned%20to%20the%20office%202%20days%20per%20week%20and%20use%20AI%20to%20help%20me%20type.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221786%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Sarah%20de%20Lagarde%20had%20an%20arm%20and%20a%20leg%20amputated%20after%20two%20London%20Underground%20trains%20hit%20her%20in%20September%202022.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F652d4a4d6561dd877e7b47ba%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESarah%20de%20Lagarde%20had%20an%20arm%20and%20a%20leg%20amputated%20after%20two%20London%20Underground%20trains%20hit%20her%20in%20September%202022.%3Cp%3ETori%20Ferenc%20for%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ESarah%20de%20Lagarde%20had%20two%20amputations%20after%20two%20London%20Underground%20trains%20hit%20her%20in%20September%202022.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EShe%20returned%20to%20work%20just%20four%20months%20after%20the%20accident%2C%20which%20she%20said%20was%20important%20to%20claim%20herself%20back.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EDe%20Lagarde%20says%20her%20employer%20is%20flexible%20in%20when%20and%20where%20she%20works%2C%20and%20she%20uses%20AI%20to%20help.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20article%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Sarah%20de%20Lagarde%2C%20a%20communications%20professional%20who%20had%20an%20arm%20and%20a%20leg%20amputated%20after%20two%20London%20Underground%20trains%20hit%20her%20in%20September%202022.%20It%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flondon-underground-tube-accident-lost-limbs-amputate-daughter-takes-tube-2023-10%3Fr%3DUS%26IR%3DT%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EI%20had%20to%20have%20an%20arm%20and%20a%20leg%20amputated%20last%20year%20following%20an%20accident%20on%20the%20London%20Underground%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20spent%20two%20weeks%20in%20a%20trauma%20ward%20and%20six%20in%20a%20rehabilitation%20ward%2C%20learning%20to%20walk%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20a%20year%20after%20the%20accident%2C%20I'm%20working%20three%20days%20a%20week%2C%20two%20of%20which%20are%20spent%20in%20the%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20told%20that%20most%20patients%20in%20my%20situation%20would%20not%20consider%20returning%20to%20work%20until%20two%20or%20three%20years%20after%20the%20accident.%20I%20returned%20four%20months%20after%20the%20accident%20to%20my%20role%20in%20communications%20at%20an%20asset-management%20group%2C%20well%20before%20I%20got%20my%20bionic%20arm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221786%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Sarah%20de%20Lagarde%20had%20an%20arm%20and%20a%20leg%20amputated%20after%20two%20London%20Underground%20trains%20hit%20her%20in%20September%202022.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F652d4a898bed706e837d2d3d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESarah%20de%20Lagarde%20uses%20an%20internal%20AI%20program%20for%20text%20writing%20and%20presentation%20building%20to%20help%20with%20her%20work%20as%20a%20communications%20professional%20after%20the%20accident.%20%3Cp%3ETori%20Ferenc%20for%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20colleagues%20were%20absolutely%20amazing%20in%20supporting%20me%20in%20my%20darkest%20hour.%20So%20many%20employees%20had%20been%20in%20touch%2C%20sent%20me%20cards%2C%20messages%2C%20presents.%20I%20felt%20really%20supported.%20That%20was%20amazing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20wanted%20to%20go%20back%20because%20I%20knew%20that%20I%20would%20have%20psychological%20safety%20and%20acceptance.%20And%20of%20course%20remuneration%20plays%20a%20part%20as%20well.%20In%20the%20first%20instance%2C%20though%2C%20it%20was%20knowing%20that%20my%20colleagues%20would%20be%20welcoming%20me%20and%20that%20is%20hugely%20important.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20beginning%2C%20I%20could%20only%20work%20two%20days%20a%20week%2C%20mainly%20due%20to%20the%20numerous%20medical%20appointments%20I%20had.%20But%20now%20I%20work%20three%20days%20a%20week%2C%20with%20two%20in%20the%20office%2C%20and%20I'll%20look%20to%20increase%20that%20as%20we%20go%20on.%20As%20I%20get%20fewer%20medical%20appointments%2C%20I%20can%20increase%20my%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20employer%20has%20been%20flexible%20in%20working%20hours%20and%20remote%20work.%20I've%20got%20the%20option%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwork-from-home-remote-work-changed-economy-pandemic-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ework%20from%20home%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20but%20going%20into%20the%20office%20was%20very%20important%20to%20me%20because%20I%20could%20feel%20the%20support%2C%20I%20could%20talk%20to%20my%20colleagues%2C%20I%20could%20welcome%20those%20hugs%20and%20words%20of%20support%2C%20but%20also%20it%20took%20me%20out%20of%20my%20home.%20It%20allowed%20me%20to%20claim%20myself%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20love%20my%20job.%20I've%20been%20doing%20this%20job%20for%2020%20years.%20I've%20spent%20so%20much%20time%20investing%20in%20the%20companies%20that%20I%20work%20for%2C%20in%20my%20relationships%20with%20my%20colleagues.%20Going%20from%20being%20able%20to%20disabled%20in%20a%20blink%20of%20an%20eye%2C%20it%20was%20really%20important%20for%20me%20to%20claim%20that%20part%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20take%20taxis%20to%20work%2C%20which%20is%20quite%20expensive.%20I%20haven't%20taken%20public%20transport%20since%20the%20accident%20and%20the%20sound%20of%20trains%20terrifies%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20can%20be%20frank%20and%20honest%20with%20my%20colleagues%20about%20the%20things%20I%20can%20do%20and%20the%20things%20I%20can't%20do%2C%20and%20we%20have%20collaboratively%20devised%20a%20plan%20as%20to%20how%20things%20can%20work%20for%20the%20best.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20company%20made%20small%20adjustments%20so%20I%20can%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20my%20dominant%20arm%20was%20amputated%2C%20I%20had%20to%20start%20writing%20with%20my%20non-dominant%20hand%20after%20the%20accident.%20Though%20the%20handwriting's%20readable%2C%20it's%20not%20that%20great.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20know%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsoftbank-ceo-masayoshi-son-on-ai-doubters-being-left-behind-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI%20is%20heavily%20debated%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20in%20my%20case%20it's%20a%20support%2C%20such%20as%20its%20speech-to-text%20functions.%20I%20use%20an%20internal%20AI%20program%20for%20text%20writing%20and%20presentation%20building.%20So%20in%20essence%2C%20I%20can%20do%20the%20same%20tasks%20as%20I%20did%20before%20using%20AI%20technology.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flondon-underground-tube-amputate-return-office-home-remote-work-ai-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697549135000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F652d4b668bed706e837d2e95%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flondon-underground-tube-amputate-return-office-home-remote-work-ai-2023-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Sarah%20de%20Lagarde%20said%20that%20returning%20to%20work%20after%20her%20double%20amputation%20%26quot%3Ballowed%20me%20to%20claim%20myself%20back.%26quot%3B%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22gdean%40insider.com%20(Grace%20Dean)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flondon-underground-tube-amputate-return-office-home-remote-work-ai-2023-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Reclining%20Seats%2C%20Big%20Windows%3A%20First%20Look%20Inside%20Delhi-Meerut%20RapidX%20Coach%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20priority%20stretch%20of%20the%20Delhi-Meerut%20Rapid%20Rail%20Transport%20System%20(RRTS)%20is%20inaugurated%20on%20Friday%2C%20passengers%20can%20look%20forward%20to%20an%20aircraft-like%20seating%20arrangement%20in%20the%20coaches%2C%20which%20have%20comfortable%2C%20reclining%20seats.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENDTV%20took%20a%20ride%20during%20a%20demonstration%20run%20of%20the%20high-speed%20RRTS%2C%20also%20known%20as%20the%20RapidX%20project%2C%20and%20got%20a%20first%20look%20at%20the%20coaches%20of%20the%20train.%20Apart%20from%20the%20reclining%20seats%20and%20large%20windows%2C%20the%20high-tech%20coaches%20will%20have%20digital%20screens%20showing%20passengers%20where%20the%20train%20is%20on%20its%20route%20at%20any%20given%20point%20of%20time%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20current%20speed%20of%20the%20train.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EEach%20rake%20will%20have%20six%20coaches%2C%20one%20premium%20and%20five%20standard.%20There%20will%20be%20a%20higher%20fare%20for%20the%20premium%20coaches%20and%20one%20of%20the%20standard%20coaches%20will%20be%20reserved%20for%20women.%20Over%2050%25%20of%20the%20staff%20will%20be%20women%20and%2C%20to%20ensure%20employment%20for%20local%20residents%2C%20preference%20will%20be%20given%20to%20people%20living%20between%20Delhi%20and%20Meerut.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThere%20will%20also%20be%20a%20waiting%20lounge%20at%20the%20stations%20for%20premium%20ticket%20holders.%20For%20passengers%2C%20the%20first%20train%20will%20run%20on%20Saturday%20and%20the%20frequency%20will%20be%2015%20minutes%20to%20begin%20with.%20The%20trains%20will%20stop%20at%20each%20station%20for%2030%20seconds.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20RRTS%20will%20be%20different%20from%20both%20the%20normal%20railway%20system%20and%20the%20Metro%20network%20because%20it%20will%20be%20India's%20first%20railway%20system%20to%20have%20a%20maximum%20operational%20speed%20of%20160%20kilometres%20per%20hour.%20There%20will%20be%2014%20stations%20on%20the%20route%20and%20the%20average%20speed%20is%20expected%20to%20be%20100%20kmph.%20The%20maximum%20speed%20reached%20by%20the%20train%20during%20the%20demonstration%20run%20was%20146%20kmph.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPrime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20will%20inaugurate%20the%2017-km%20Sahibabad%20to%20Duhai%20Depot%20section%20of%20the%20corridor%2C%20which%20has%20a%20total%20of%20five%20stations%20-%20Sahibabad%2C%20Ghaziabad%2C%20Guldhar%2C%20Duhai%20and%20Duhai%20Depot.%20It%20will%20take%2015-17%20minutes%20to%20cover%20this%20distance.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20entire%20corridor%20of%20the%20Rs%2030%2C274-crore%20project%20will%20be%2082-km%20long%20and%20stretch%20from%20Sarai%20Kale%20Khan%20station%20in%20Delhi%20to%20Modipuram%20in%20Meerut.%20The%20time%20taken%20between%20Meerut%20and%20Delhi%20in%20a%20mail%20express%20train%20is%20one-and-a-half%20hours%20and%20two%20hours%20in%20a%20local%20train%2C%20but%20the%20RRTS%20will%20only%20take%2055-60%20minutes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20entire%20section%20is%20expected%20to%20be%20completed%20in%20June%202025.%20The%20foundation%20stone%20of%20the%20project%20had%20been%20laid%20by%20PM%20Modi%20on%20March%208%2C%202019.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697549100000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-10%2Fu8ksrlp8_delhi-meerut-rrts-coach-650_625x300_17_October_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Freclining-seats-big-windows-first-look-inside-delhi-meerut-rrts-coach-4489733%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22After%20the%20priority%20stretch%20of%20the%20Delhi-Meerut%20Rapid%20Rail%20Transport%20System%20(RRTS)%20is%20inaugurated%20on%20Friday%2C%20passengers%20can%20look%20forward%20to%20an%20aircraft-like%20seating%20arrangement%20in%20the%20coaches%2C%20which%20have%20comfortable%2C%20reclining%20seats.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Freclining-seats-big-windows-first-look-inside-delhi-meerut-rrts-coach-4489733%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Freclining-seats-big-windows-first-look-inside-delhi-meerut-rrts-coach-4489733%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fr