960%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Russia%20Lancet%20drone%20Ukraine%20Zaporizhzhia%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F652d305655f52b01b3601eb3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Russian%20Lancet%20loitering%20munition%20shot%20down%20in%20the%20Zaporizhzhia%20region%20in%20July%202022.%3Cp%3EStrategic%20Communications%20Directorate%20of%20the%20Ukrainian%20Armed%20Forces%2FHandout%20via%20REUTERS%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EUnveiled%20in%202019%2C%20the%20Lancet%20is%20Russia's%20first%20purpose-built%20loitering%20munition.%20The%20Lancet-3%20is%20made%20by%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fzala.aero%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EZala%20Aero%20Group%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20subsidiary%20of%20the%20Kalashnikov%20concern%2C%20and%20it%20comes%20in%20two%20varieties.%20The%20smaller%20Izdeliye-52%20has%20two%20conspicuous%20X-shaped%20wings%20and%20carries%20a%206.5-pound%20warhead%2C%20while%20the%20Izdeliye-51%20has%20an%2011-pound%20warhead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20being%20used%20on%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.armyrecognition.com%2Fdefense_news_april_2021_global_security_army_industry%2Frussian_lancet_loitering_munitions_tested_in_syria.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etrial%20basis%20in%20Syria%20in%202021%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Lancet%20was%20rushed%20into%20full-scale%20service%20for%20this%20conflict.%20The%20first%20known%20use%20in%20Ukraine%20was%20in%20July%202022%2C%20some%20five%20months%20into%20the%20invasion.%20Since%20then%20it%20has%20been%20used%20in%20small%20but%20growing%20numbers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20used%20sparingly%2C%20most%20likely%20by%20the%20SOF%20%5BSpecial%20Operations%20Forces%5D%20and%20similar%20units%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fsambendett%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESamuel%20Bendett%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20an%20analyst%20with%20the%20CNA%2C%20CNAS%2C%20and%20CSIS%20told%2019FortyFive.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20their%20use%20is%20creating%20difficulties%20for%20the%20Ukrainian%20military.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20first%20only%20a%20handful%20of%20Lancet%20strike%20videos%20were%20posted%20each%20month.%20But%20this%20January%2C%2022%20Lancet%20attack%20videos%20appeared.%20That%20number%20rose%20to%2062%20in%20May%2C%20and%20124%20in%20August.%20The%20makers%20claim%20they%20are%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdzen.ru%2Fvideo%2Fwatch%2F6492e62e89454b7ee9646c13%3Ft%3D5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emass-producing%20the%20weapon%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20a%20new%20facility%2C%20so%20what%20we%20are%20seeing%20now%20is%20only%20the%20start.%20This%20growth%20in%20production%20is%20taking%20place%20despite%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20Lancet%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.forbes.com%2Fsites%2Fdavidhambling%2F2023%2F03%2F28%2Fdoes-russias-smartest-weapon-have-an-american-brain%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Euses%20Western-made%20electronics%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20in%20theory%20should%20be%20impossible%20for%20Russia%20to%20obtain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20signs%20that%20the%20Russian%20defense%20industry%20is%20ramping%20up%20Lancet%20production%2C%20along%20with%20improvements%20that%20lead%20to%20more%20advanced%20designs%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Bendett.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Lancet%20is%20launched%20from%20a%20catapult%20rail%20and%20transmits%20video%20back%20to%20the%20operator.%20Lancets%20are%20reportedly%20flown%20in%20conjunction%20with%20reconnaissance%20drones%20which%20spot%20targets%20and%20relay%20coordinates.%20The%20Lancet%20operator%20flies%20to%20the%20target%20area%2C%20visually%20confirms%20the%20target%2C%20and%20carries%20out%20the%20strike.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20electric%20propeller%20drives%20the%20Lancet%20at%20around%2070%20mph.%20This%20slow%20speed%20makes%20it%20an%20easier%20target%20than%20a%20guided%20missile%20or%20other%20munition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEvery%20day%20we%20shoot%20down%20at%20least%20one%20or%20two%20of%20these%20Lancets%2C%26quot%3B%20Yuriy%20Sak%2C%20an%20adviser%20to%20Ukraine's%20defense%20minister%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rferl.org%2Fa%2Flancet-drones-russia-invasion-counteroffensive-kamikaze%2F32493513.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20Reuters%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BBut%20it's%20not%20a%20100%20percent%20interception%20rate%2C%20unfortunately.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarly%20Lancet%20attacks%20were%20all%20on%20static%20targets.%20More%20recent%20videos%20have%20shown%20hits%20on%20moving%20vehicles.%20This%20may%20indicate%20a%20change%20in%20doctrine%20or%20an%20improvement%20in%20operator%20skill%20levels.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20even%20now%20Lancets%20frequently%20miss.%20Videos%20posted%20online%20usually%20show%20successful%20attacks%2C%20but%20in%20the%20case%20of%20Lancets%2C%20optimistic%20posters%20sometimes%20put%20up%20videos%20that%20on%20close%20inspection%20turn%20out%20to%20be%20near-misses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussian%20open%20source%20analysts%20Lost%20Armor%20have%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flostarmour.info%2Ftags%2Flancet%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecompiled%20and%20classified%20every%20known%20Lancet%20strike%20video%3C%2Fa%3E%20online.%20About%207%25%20of%20Lancet%20attack%20videos%20clearly%20show%20misses%2C%20and%20in%20another%208%25%20it%20is%20impossible%20to%20tell%20if%20the%20target%20is%20actually%20hit.%20A%20small%20number%20of%20videos%2C%20perhaps%201%25%20of%20the%20total%2C%20show%20Lancets%20hitting%20what%20are%20identifiable%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pravda.com.ua%2Feng%2Fnews%2F2023%2F06%2F12%2F7406490%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eas%20inflatable%20or%20wooden%20dummies%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20rest%20are%20doing%20real%20damage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ETarget%20set%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Russia%20Lancet%20drone%20Ukraine%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F652d30558bed706e837d1262%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221121%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUkrainian%20soldiers%20shoot%20at%20what%20Ukraine%20said%20were%20Russian%20Lancet%20drones%20in%20a%20still%20image%20from%20a%20video%20released%20in%20May.%3Cp%3EUkraine%20Defense%20Ministry%2FHandout%20via%20REUTERS%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feuromaidanpress.com%2F2023%2F08%2F17%2Fukraine-develops-autonomous-fpv-drones-photos%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOne%20Ukrainian%20analyst%3C%2Fa%3E%20puts%20the%20success%20rate%20of%20the%20Lancet%20at%20approximately%2025%25-30%25%2C%20suggesting%20that%20there%20are%20a%20couple%20of%20misses%20or%20shootdowns%20for%20each%20of%20the%20strike%20videos%20seen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flostarmour.info%2Ftags%2Flancet%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20Lost%20Armor%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20as%20of%20October%203%20there%20are%20667%20Lancet%20strike%20videos.%20Of%20these%2C%20210%20are%20classed%20as%20target%20destroyed%20(31%25)%2C%20355%20target%20damaged%20(53%25)%2C%2048%20miss%20(7%25)%2C%20and%2052%20are%20unknown%20(7%25).%20In%20particular%2C%20the%20heavy%20armor%20of%20tanks%20sometimes%20shrugs%20off%20the%20Lancet's%20relatively%20small%20warhead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20suggests%20that%20around%202%2C000%20Lancets%20have%20destroyed%20200%20targets%20and%20damaged%20hundreds.%20That%20may%20seem%20low%2C%20but%20with%20each%20Lancet%20costing%20perhaps%20%2435%2C000%20and%20each%20target%20costing%20millions%2C%20the%20Lancet%20is%20extremely%20cost-effective.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwenty-five%20percent%20of%20the%20targets%20comprised%20tanks%20and%20lighter%20armored%20vehicles%20%E2%80%94%20in%20at%20least%20one%20case%2C%20a%20German-supplied%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3D9M-XfZl3TGE%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELeopard-2%20tank%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Analysts%20suggest%20that%20the%20Leopard%20was%20already%20immobilized%20by%20a%20mine%20or%20missile%20before%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aroged.com%2F2023%2F08%2F03%2Faroged-lancet-kamikaze-drone-successfully-hit-another-leopard-2-tank%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebeing%20finished%20off%20by%20the%20Lancet%3C%2Fa%3E.%20As%20in%20the%20other%20videos%2C%20the%20tank%20is%20observed%20by%20a%20Russian%20drone%20before%2C%20during%2C%20and%20after%20the%20strike.%20Whether%20or%20not%20the%20Lancet%20was%20the%20sole%20cause%20of%20destruction%2C%20this%20episode%20suggests%20that%20even%20the%20latest%20and%20best%20-protected%20armor%20is%20vulnerable%20to%20Lancet%20strikes%20from%20long%20range.%20If%20you%20accept%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2F247wallst.com%2Ftechnology-3%2F2023%2F01%2F21%2Fgermans-leopard-2-cost-11-million%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evalue%20of%20%2411%20million%20for%20a%20Leopard-2%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20that's%20about%20300%20Lancets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETen%20percent%20of%20the%20targets%20were%20motor%20vehicles%20and%20other%20relatively%20low-value%20targets.%20These%20may%20have%20been%20selected%20when%20a%20Lancet%20failed%20to%20find%20its%20intended%20target%20(or%20this%20had%20already%20been%20destroyed)%2C%20or%20where%20a%20vehicle%20carrying%20ammunition%20was%20considered%20a%20priority.%20Cheap%20FPV%20drones%20costing%20a%20few%20hundred%20dollars%20apiece%20are%20far%20better%20suited%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.forbes.com%2Fsites%2Fdavidhambling%2F2023%2F08%2F02%2Fthe-fast-and-furious-fpv-drone-strikes-on-russias-supply-lines%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etask%20of%20hitting%20enemy%20transport%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20troops%20in%20trenches.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%2015%25%20of%20the%20targets%20were%20very%20high%20value%3A%20Ukrainian%20surface-to-air%20missile%20launchers%20and%20radar%20systems.%20These%20are%20typically%20kept%20several%20miles%20back%20from%20the%20front%20line%2C%20but%20not%20far%20enough%20to%20be%20out%20of%20Lancet%20range.%20Knocking%20these%20out%20allows%20Russia%20to%20use%20its%20air%20superiority%20in%20helicopters%20and%20strike%20aircraft%20on%20the%20battlefield.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20artillery%20killer%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ukraine%20artillery%20in%20Zaporizhzhia%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F63a320faae4bde0019502de8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221331%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUkrainian%20troops%20fire%20a%20howitzer%20in%20the%20Zaporizhzhia%20region%20in%20December%202022.%3Cp%3EDmytro%20Smoliyenko%20%2F%20Ukrinform%2FFuture%20Publishing%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20far%20the%20largest%20number%20of%20Lancet%20strike%20videos%20show%20attacks%20on%20Ukrainian%20artillery%2C%20both%20towed%20and%20self-propelled%20guns.%20As%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Frusi.org%2Fexplore-our-research%2Fpublications%2Fcommentary%2Frussias-artillery-war-ukraine-challenges-and-innovations%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecent%20report%20from%20UK%20defense%20think%20tank%20RUSI%3C%2Fa%3E%20notes%2C%20Russian%20forces%20now%20use%20the%20Lancet%20extensively%20as%20a%20counter-battery%20weapon.%20Artillery%20is%20the%20traditional%20means%20of%20striking%20enemy%20artillery%2C%20but%20the%20long%20range%20of%20the%20Lancet%2C%20and%20its%20ability%20to%20seek%20out%20hidden%20targets%20on%20the%20ground%2C%20give%20it%20real%20advantages.%20Additionally%2C%20the%20Lancet%20operator%20remains%20hidden%20and%20will%20not%20be%20targeted%20by%20counter-battery%20fire.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELost%20Armor%20counts%20142%20hits%20on%20self-propelled%20artillery%20and%20170%20on%20guns%20and%20mortars.%20These%20are%20significant%20numbers.%20According%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.oryxspioenkop.com%2F2022%2F02%2Fattack-on-europe-documenting-ukrainian.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edatabase%20compiled%20by%20open-source%20analysts%20Oryx%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Ukraine%20has%20suffered%20222%20self-propelled%20guns%20destroyed%20or%20damaged.%20This%20suggests%20that%20Lancets%20may%20be%20responsible%20for%2064%25%20of%20Ukrainian%20self-propelled%20gun%20losses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20proportion%20for%20towed%20artillery%20appears%20unbelievably%20high%3A%20169%20hits%2C%20compared%20to%20the%20160%20destroyed%20or%20damaged%20and%20recorded%20by%20Oryx.%20Towed%20artillery%20is%20much%20harder%20to%20destroy%20than%20a%20self-propelled%20gun%2C%20even%20when%20hit.%20The%20latter%20is%20a%20tracked%20vehicle%20with%20a%20store%20of%20flammable%20fuel%20and%20explosive%20ammunition%20on%20board%2C%20either%20of%20which%20can%20be%20set%20off%20by%20a%20Lancet%20strike.%20A%20towed%20artillery%20piece%2C%20by%20contrast%2C%20is%20a%20more%20solid%20piece%20of%20machinery%20able%20to%20survive%20the%20blast%20and%20minor%20shrapnel%20fragments%20of%20a%20Lancet%20hit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20lethality%20of%20Lancet%20is%20often%20insufficient%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Frusi.org%2Fexplore-our-research%2Fpublications%2Fcommentary%2Frussias-artillery-war-ukraine-challenges-and-innovations%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20the%20RUSI%20report%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BOne%20officer%20also%20said%20that%20although%20he%20had%20seen%20his%20gun%20'destroyed'%20several%20times%20online%2C%20it%20remained%20alive%20and%20well.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20tallies%20with%20previous%20conflicts%20in%20which%20towed%20artillery%20has%20proven%20more%20robust%20to%20counter-battery%20fire.%20Crews%20may%20be%20injured%20or%20killed%2C%20but%20the%20guns%20themselves%20tend%20to%20survive%20and%20remain%20serviceable.%20In%20WWII%2C%20the%20loss%20rate%20for%20self-propelled%20guns%20was%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.dupuyinstitute.org%2Fblog%2F2022%2F10%2F31%2Fresponse-to-question-on-dupuys-combat-attrition-verities%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etwo%20to%20three%20times%20higher%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20for%20towed%20artillery.%20So%20many%20of%20the%20Lancet%20hits%20on%20towed%20artillery%20likely%20did%20not%20result%20in%20kills.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20claim%20in%20May%20by%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.easternherald.com%2F2023%2F04%2F06%2Frussian-lancet-drones-destroyed-almost-half-of-nato-artillery-in-the-nvo-area%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERussia's%20RIA%20Novosti%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Lancet-3s%20had%20destroyed%2045%25%20of%20Ukraine's%20Western-supplied%20artillery%20is%20likely%20a%20wild%20exaggeration%20based%20on%20this%20sort%20of%20overcounting.%20But%20it%20is%20clear%20that%20a%20high%20proportion%20of%20Ukrainian%20artillery%20losses%20are%20from%20Lancets%2C%20and%20those%20losses%20are%20likely%20to%20increase%20as%20more%20Lancets%20are%20deployed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHard%20lessons%20ahead%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Russia%20Orlan-10%20Granat-3%20Shahed-136%20Eleron-3-SV%20drones%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F63fcde45ae0bf0001824d993%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221466%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUkrainian%20officials%20display%20an%20Orlan-10%20and%20other%20Russian%20drones%20at%20a%20briefing%20in%20Kyiv%20in%20December%202022.%3Cp%3ESTR%2FNurPhoto%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20situation%20in%20Ukraine%20is%20evolving%20fast%2C%20and%20the%20effectiveness%20of%20Lancets%20and%20other%20loitering%20munitions%20may%20yet%20be%20blunted.%20Ukrainian%20artillery%20crews%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.forbes.com%2Fsites%2Fsebastienroblin%2F2023%2F01%2F31%2Fukraine-uses-camouflage-nets-to-snare-russian-drones-attacking-its-artillery%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Euse%20protective%20nets%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20have%20some%20success%20in%20stopping%20Lancets.%20Jammers%20are%20now%20issued%20widely%2C%20but%20it%20is%20not%20clear%20how%20effective%20they%20are.%20The%20Lancets%2C%20and%20the%20defensive%20measures%20used%20to%20stop%20them%2C%20will%20both%20probably%20improve.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20far%2C%20the%20Lancet's%20main%20limitation%20seems%20to%20be%20limited%20numbers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20still%20not%20enough%20of%20them%20to%20saturate%20the%20front%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Bendett%2C%20noting%20commentary%20in%20Russian%20military%20Telegram%20about%20the%20demand%20for%20more%20such%20drones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20concern%20is%20that%20the%20Lancet's%20range%20is%20being%20stretched.%20In%20September%2C%20a%20Russian%20Lancet%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsputnikglobe.com%2F20230921%2Fhow-russian-lancet-drone-surgically-struck-ukraininan-jets-cockpit-from-80-km-1113549589.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edestroyed%20a%20parked%20Ukrainian%20MiG-29%20jet%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20a%20range%20of%20at%20least%2050%20miles.%20According%20to%20Russian%20media%2C%20this%20was%20achieved%20with%20the%20aid%20of%20unspecified%20design%20modifications.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20success%20of%20the%20Lancet%20has%20also%20inspired%20a%20number%20of%20Russian%20companies%20and%20volunteer%20groups%20to%20produce%20low-cost%20Lancet%20look-alikes.%20These%20offer%20similar%20capabilities%20for%20a%20fraction%20of%20the%20cost.%20According%20to%20makers%2C%20they%20could%20be%20fielded%20by%20the%20thousands.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20rivals%20include%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fvostok-kb.ru%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESkalpel%3C%2Fa%3E%20made%20by%20the%20Vostok%20design%20bureau%2C%20and%20the%20Oko%20company's%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Foko-kb.ru%2F%23mainBlock%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPrivet-82%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Both%20companies%20say%20they%20can%20mass-produce%20as%20soon%20as%20they%20get%20an%20order.%20Volunteer%20group%20Archangel%20has%20also%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fsambendett%2Fstatus%2F1666060690153431042%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eproduced%20a%20prototype%20fixed-wing%20loitering%20munition%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20they%20say%20is%20much%20cheaper%20than%20the%20Lancet.%20Bendett%20notes%20that%20competitors%20tend%20to%20have%20shorter%20range%20%E2%80%94%20around%2025%20miles%20or%20less.%20Though%20less%20sophisticated%2C%20they%20may%20still%20be%20dangerous.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZala%20clearly%20aims%20to%20produce%20a%20lot%20more%20loitering%20munitions%2C%20and%20the%20company%20has%20already%20shown%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fsambendett%2Fstatus%2F1680576870226460673%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evideo%20of%20a%20Lancet%20swarm%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20which%20one%20operator%20controls%20several%20Lancets%20in%20a%20simultaneous%20strike.%20This%20would%20increase%20the%20chances%20that%20at%20least%20one%20gets%20through.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBendett%20notes%20that%20Zala%20has%20a%20well%20established%20relationship%20with%20the%20Russian%20government%20and%20military%2C%20so%20others%20may%20struggle%20to%20break%20into%20the%20market.%20But%20with%20increased%20Lancet%20production%20and%20several%20other%20possible%20contenders%20also%20pushing%20loitering%20munitions%2C%20we%20are%20likely%20to%20see%20far%20more%20strikes%20from%20this%20type%20of%20weapon%20in%20the%20coming%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20its%20part%2C%20Ukraine%20has%20used%20large%20numbers%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.forbes.com%2Fsites%2Fdavidhambling%2F2023%2F05%2F05%2Fpilots-not-dronesukraines-escadrone-on-the-skill-of-flying-fpv-kamikazes%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esmall%20FPV%20kamikazes%20to%20great%20effect%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20we%20have%20yet%20to%20see%20anything%20on%20their%20side%20with%20the%20size%20and%20range%20of%20the%20Lancet.%20This%20is%20likely%20to%20change%20in%20the%20very%20near%20future.%20The%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.forbes.com%2Fsites%2Fdavidhambling%2F2022%2F08%2F02%2Fhas-elusive-phoenix-ghost-loitering-munition-broken-cover-at-last%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshadowy%20US-supplied%20Phoenix%20Ghost%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20of%20which%20there%20are%20no%20known%20images%2C%20may%20be%20the%20nearest%20current%20equivalent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELoitering%20munitions%20do%20not%20make%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.19fortyfive.com%2F2023%2F09%2Fukraines-smallest-drones-are-decimating-russias-heavy-artillery%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etanks%20or%20artillery%20obsolete%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20they%20may%20push%20casualties%20higher%20and%20drive%20new%20types%20of%20thinking%20and%20new%20styles%20of%20warfare.%20There%20are%20hard%20lessons%20to%20be%20learned%2C%20for%20Ukraine%20and%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EAbout%20the%20author%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDavid%20Hambling%20is%20a%20London-based%20journalist%2C%20author%2C%20and%20consultant%20specializing%20in%20defense%20technology%20with%20over%2020%20years'%20experience.%20He%20writes%20for%20Aviat